From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 09:45:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Use HiFi id for standard Sony mono endpoint.

Spider-Man Remastered's working controller-effect path used the standard Sony
controller speaker identity derived from the Pulse `HiFi__Speaker__sink` name.
Using the newer `Default__Speaker__sink` alias gives the same physical sink a
different Windows endpoint GUID, so the game probes the mono speaker but never
initializes it for effect playback when the controller is already connected at
startup.

Keep the standard DualSense/DualShock logical speaker endpoint on the old HiFi
identity while retaining the separate DualSense Edge endpoint identity added
earlier. This only changes the app-facing endpoint id; streams are still routed
to the actual connected Pulse sink.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 88888888888..99999999999 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -1313,7 +1313,7 @@ static BOOL pulse_stream_dualsense_mono_format(const struct pulse_stream *stream
 }
 
 #define DUALSENSE_MONO_ENDPOINT_ID \
-    "alsa_output.usb-Sony_Interactive_Entertainment_Wireless_Controller-00.Default__Speaker__sink"
+    "alsa_output.usb-Sony_Interactive_Entertainment_Wireless_Controller-00.HiFi__Speaker__sink"
 #define DUALSENSE_EDGE_MONO_ENDPOINT_ID \
     "alsa_output.usb-Sony_Interactive_Entertainment_DualSense_Edge_Wireless_Controller-00.Default__Speaker__sink"
 
